v3.3.1b 1st June 2022
        - problem with acro package and hyperref resolved
        - cover for dissertations slightly changed
v3.3.1 25th May 2022
        - TeXLive 2022 support
        - extended affidavit
        - updated list of package versions
v3.3   10th March 2022
	- modifications to account for changes in the chemmacros package
	- versions of used packages defined in the appendix to simplify the search for errors when the template does not compile successfully
	- minor changes in the citation style
	- addition of the optidef package for the formulation of optimization problems
	- modifications of the siunitx options regarding the language specifications
v3.2   12th October 2021
        - switched from tabu to supertabular for list of abbreviations
        - changed SI commands to account for changes in siunitx v3.X
        - definition of an s column with the collcell package as this column type has been removed from siunitx v3.X
        - updated package dependency and command tables in the appendices
v3.1.4 22nd March 2021
	- default language changed back to German
v3.1.3 1st February 2021
        - links updated to new git domain of TU Berlin
v3.1.2 20th November 2020
        - textcite redefined to include shorthands, e.g., for citing norms
        - short explanation for shorthands added
v3.1.1 18th November 2020
        - tabu environment for list of abbreviations exchanged by longtabu as tabu environment does no page break
v3.1    13th October 2020
        - template features and structure redone and shortened
v3.0.5  7th October 2020
        - as Overleaf now supports the TeXLive 2020 compiler, the comment to the old commit of this project was removed
        - the template can now be used directly with Overleaf with no additional changes
v3.0.4  5th August 2020
        - reference to mathcha.io added in section on vector graphics
        - uniquelist and uniquename were both set to false. Hence, Smith, John, and Mueller (2011) and Smith, Johnson, and Maier (2012) will now result in Smith et al. (2011) or Smith et al. (2012)
v3.0.3  18th June 2020
        - exchanged markboth, addcontensline, chapter* by addchap in h_abbreviations.tex
        - documentation for list of abbreviations improved
